-------------------------------------------------------------------

     ============================================================
     A Geant4 example to read simulate INO prototype with CRY Data
     ============================================================

     This code requires the installation of Geant4.11.1 and ROOT 6.20
     
     The data from CRY simulation is stored in a root file. A sample root file
     can be found inside the data folder.
     
     -Create a build directory name 'build' and generate makefiles (using cmake or cmake-gui) from within this directory
     -Copy all the contents of 'data' folder to 'build' folder including the C files
     -Compile the Geant4 code as usual using make -j4
     -Run the code using ./exampleB1
     -The code reads the input data from test.root and outputs in output.root
     -The code readfile.C can be used to analyse the input test.root file: 
     -- Run using root test.root
     -The code readOutput.C can be used to analyse the output file output.root.
     -- Run using root output.root
     
     
     


